    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "666284d7_6b14357c",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/control/bugreport_agent.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 26,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-13T22:59:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "what\u0027s the purpose of this agent? Agents as of now serve two purposes:\n1. Isolate engine-specific code (qemu1, qemu2) from the AndroidEmu library, to make sure AndroidEmu remains generic and doesn\u0027t need to call into an engine directly\n2. Isolate the non-UI part of AndroidEmu library from the UI part, to make sure emulator is able to run without UI.\n\nBugreport object, as I see in the CL, is a part of a generic non-UI AndroidEmu library. It\u0027s totally OK for the UI code to call into it directly - e.g. Qt code already uses metrics reporter and crash reporter directly\n\nAnother question is why do we need to have a C interface for a bug reporter? As of now, I only see C++ code initializing it and calling into it. C interfaces are legacy interfaces, they remain from the times when most of the code was in C. We still need to create them if a C source needs to call into a service, but here I only see emulator Qt window (and Qt no-window) use it. Is there a way to expose the C++ interface directly?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 26,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "920aeef4673587ed5c896419d8d640b656ea2197",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "f92a3ee7_d7e04c1f",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/control/bugreport_agent.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 26,
      "author": {
        "id": 1121388
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-19T18:33:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "In response to the purpose of this agent. \nActually, Bugreport object is compiled into the emulator-libui module instead of android-emu module because bugreport agent requires QT library. Thus, the bugreport agent is NOT isolating non-UI from UI. I think it\u0027d be okay to make the bugreport agent not relying on the QT library by moving the sendToGoolge logic into the UI code. \n\nIn response to the use case:\nanother use case is for the console command, where console.c needs a C-interface.",
      "parentUuid": "666284d7_6b14357c",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 26,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "920aeef4673587ed5c896419d8d640b656ea2197",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "98aeea8c_73e79cbb",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/emulation/control/bugreport_agent.h",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 26,
      "author": {
        "id": 1080076
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-07-29T02:00:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the explanations.\n\nI believe that the bug reporting logic should not rely on the UI or Qt library, it should only be responsible for preparing the data to send. Then, UI or something else would wrap the methods and call them when to show the data to the user and send it to our bug tracker.\n\nRegarding the C interface, there\u0027s no need to make it an agent - just create a C wrapper interface for the required functions, as in FeatureControl.h/cpp and feature_control.h.\nAgents complicate lots of things, like tracking down what is there and where it gets set, and why do we need that another level of abstraction.\nFor the ui-non ui isolation, or to hide the engine interface from the rest of AndroidEmu library it\u0027s OK. Calling from one part of AndroidEmu into another one using a C agent needs to be solving some really complex problem.\n\nActually, let me check if I can just make the console.c code C++ now to get rid of that C interface requirement",
      "parentUuid": "f92a3ee7_d7e04c1f",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 20,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 26,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "920aeef4673587ed5c896419d8d640b656ea2197",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    }
